This analysis detects scanf-family formats that read unbounded strings.
1. Does the format string contain %s or %[ without a width limit?
2. What is the destination buffer size at the call site?
3. Is input attacker-controlled or externally influenced?
4. Are there independent bounds checks that make overflow impossible?
Use the tools to inspect format literals, destination types, and caller constraints.
If effective bounds are guaranteed, there is no issue.
Only flag if unbounded reads can overflow destination storage.
